parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine overheating and stalling can cause the vehicle to lose power and stall, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of an accident.
symptoms: The vehicle overheats
stalls
and may restart after cooling down
but the failure may occur intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine knocking or failure can cause the engine to seize, leading to a loss of power and control, and potentially causing an accident.
symptoms: Knocking or unusual noises coming from the engine
engine failure
or loss of power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Head gasket failure can cause coolant to leak into the crankcase, leading to engine damage, overheating, and potentially causing an accident.
symptoms: Heavy loss of coolant
scoring of the crankshaft and connecting rod bearings
engine failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unintended acceleration of the vehicle can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and unexpectedly
often from a complete stop
as if the gas pedal has been floored; the engine races even after the vehicle has been brought to a stop; the problem may resolve itself after restarting the engine
but can recur.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping and failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates when shifting gears
the vehicle loses power or acceleration
the vehicle stalls or dies
the transmission makes unusual noises or vibrations
the "check engine" or "transmission" light illuminates on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty transmission solenoid can cause the transmission to malfunction, leading to slipping, hesitation, or failure, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates when shifting gears
the vehicle loses power or acceleration
the vehicle stalls or dies
the transmission makes unusual noises or vibrations
the "check engine" or "transmission" light illuminates on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission control module can cause the transmission to malfunction, leading to slipping, hesitation, or failure, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates when shifting gears
the vehicle loses power or acceleration
the vehicle stalls or dies
the transmission makes unusual noises or vibrations
the "check engine" or "transmission" light illuminates on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden detachment of the vehicle's roof while driving can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The roof of the vehicle separates or flies off while driving
loud noise or wind rush
sudden loss of structural integrity
potential loss of control or accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the dealership to inspect and address the issue can lead to further safety risks, as the vehicle may be driven in an unsafe condition.
symptoms: Dealer refuses to inspect or repair the vehicle
lack of communication or response from the dealer
failure to provide a solution or resolution.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning ABS module can cause the vehicle to lose braking ability, leading to increased stopping distances, and potentially resulting in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The yellow ABS light and red brake light illuminate on the dashboard
a noise is heard when applying the brakes
and the brakes may fail if the issue is not addressed.
